---
import PanfactumMark from "@/components/icons/panfactum-mark.svg"
---
<section class="flex flex-col gap-4 py-12 lg:gap-8">
    <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-3">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
                  <span class="text-display-xs text-secondary font-semibold">
          pæn • fak • tm
      </span>

            <h2 class="text-display-xl font-machina font-semibold">
                Panfactum Mission
            </h2>

            <div class="text-display-xs">
                Panfactum was founded with one goal:
                <span class="font-bold">
          cut the cost of cloud computing by 99% over the next decade.
        </span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <span class="mr-8 hidden size-24 lg:block">
                 <PanfactumMark height={96}/>
        </span>

    </div>
    <div class="text-display-xs  grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-24 gap-y-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <p>
                We approach the problem from two angles:
            </p>
            <ul class="flex list-outside list-disc flex-col gap-4 pl-5">
                <li>
                    <b class="font-bold">Infrastructure Costs:</b> We maintain the free and open-source Panfactum Framework, the
                    most cost-effective way to run production-hardened workloads in the cloud.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <b class="font-bold">Labor Costs:</b> Our support organization and certified partners provide
                    end-to-end management of user's cloud environments at a fraction of the cost of the alternatives.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <p>We have seen firsthand how tackling these challenges produces a qualitative difference beyond simple cost reduction. When
            costs are a fraction of the status quo, it becomes easy to unlock new capabilities.
            </p>
            <p>In other words, a cheaper cloud is also a better cloud. We gain the headroom to integrate game-changing tooling and functionality
                that would have otherwise been cost-prohibitive to deploy and manage. </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>